Anonymous Tue 20 Feb 2024 21:51:03 No.63449501 Report
Quoted By: >>63449746 >>63449994
>>63446265
Consider building your story differently. Instead of building a proper plot, build characters, and an in depth world. Give the world an ongoing event (a war, a murder in need of solving, a bridge in need of building, it could be anything) and drop your characters into the world, adjacent to the larger conflict. Then, they will react, and change as their environment shapes them. Writing a good ending with this setup is difficult, as it comes off more akin to reality where things never really end. The journey along the way however, is made much easier, and to finish it, you just need to decide on an interesting objective for the characters.
